OSI Model
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Layer 7 - Application Layer - Defines what type of request it is (http / https)
Layer 6 - Presentation Layer - Encrypt the data
Layer 5 - Session Layer - Creates a session (cookies/ cache) with server (Till this poing it is happening in your browser) 
Layer 4 - Transport Layer - Segmentation of data. Also the protocol is idetified (TCP/UDP)
Layer 3 - Networking Layer - Data reaches router and path to transmit data is identified. for each segment IP address of source and destination is added. Segment is now called packets.
Layer 2 - Data Link Layer - From routers, we move to switches. Data is converted to Frames. Mac address of each component is added.
Layer 1 - Physical Layer - Switches are connected to Optical cable and here data is converted to electric signal.
